@startuml
title NC-Edit7 Host / Panel / Backend Architecture

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment left

package "Frontend Shared" {
  [src/main.ts\nbootstrap + service wiring] as Main
  [ServiceRegistry] as Registry
  [EventBus] as EventBus
  [BackendGateway] as Gateway
  [ExecutedProgramService] as ExecService
  [NCToolpathPlot] as PlotView
  [NCFocasTransfer] as FocasView
  [NCBottomPanel] as BottomPanel
  [NCWorkbenchPanelApp] as WorkbenchApp
  [Variables Content] as VariablesContent
  [Errors Content] as ErrorsContent
  [IHostBridgeService] as HostBridge
  [BrowserHostBridgeService] as BrowserBridge
  [VsCodeHostBridgeService] as VsCodeBridge
}

package "Web Host" {
  [WebConfigService] as WebConfig
  [NCEditorApp] as WebEditorApp
  [NCChannelPane\nembedded bottom panel enabled] as WebChannelPane
}

package "VS Code Host" {
  [Extension activate()] as ExtActivate
  [NCEditorProvider] as EditorProvider
  [FocasWebviewViewProvider\n(workbench panel host)] as WorkbenchProvider
  [VsCodeConfigService] as VsCodeConfig
  [Custom Editor Webview] as EditorWebview
  [Workbench Bottom Panel Webview] as BottomWebview
  [NCChannelPane\nembedded bottom panel disabled] as VsCodeChannelPane
}

package "Python Backend" {
  [FastAPI main.py] as FastAPI
  [CGI adapter\n/cgiserver_import] as CgiAdapter
  [FOCAS REST API\n/api/focas/*] as FocasApi
  [focas_service.py] as FocasService
}

package "External Systems" {
  [ncplot7py CGI] as Ncplot
  [FOCAS DLL / Mock Client] as FocasClient
  [Fanuc CNC] as Cnc
}

Main --> Registry
Registry --> EventBus
Registry --> Gateway
Registry --> ExecService
Registry --> HostBridge
HostBridge <|.. BrowserBridge
HostBridge <|.. VsCodeBridge

WebConfig --> Main
VsCodeConfig --> Main

WebEditorApp --> WebChannelPane
WebEditorApp --> PlotView
WebEditorApp --> FocasView : side tab
WebChannelPane --> BottomPanel
BottomPanel --> VariablesContent
BottomPanel --> ErrorsContent

ExtActivate --> EditorProvider
ExtActivate --> WorkbenchProvider
EditorProvider --> EditorWebview
WorkbenchProvider --> BottomWebview
EditorWebview --> Main
BottomWebview --> Main
EditorWebview --> VsCodeChannelPane
BottomWebview --> WorkbenchApp
WorkbenchApp --> VariablesContent
WorkbenchApp --> ErrorsContent
WorkbenchApp --> FocasView

Main --> VsCodeBridge : relay execution state
VsCodeBridge --> EditorProvider : workbench:relay message
EditorProvider --> WorkbenchProvider : forward bridge payload
WorkbenchProvider --> BottomWebview : postMessage()
BottomWebview --> WorkbenchApp : vscode:workbench-bridge

PlotView --> EventBus : subscribes plot:request
VsCodeChannelPane --> EventBus : publish plot:request
WebChannelPane --> EventBus : publish plot:request
EventBus --> PlotView : execution:completed
PlotView --> ExecService
ExecService --> Gateway : requestPlot()
FocasView --> Gateway : focasPing/connect/list/upload/download

Gateway --> FastAPI
FastAPI --> CgiAdapter
FastAPI --> FocasApi
FocasApi --> FocasService
CgiAdapter --> Ncplot
FocasService --> FocasClient
FocasClient --> Cnc

note right of WebEditorApp
Current web host:
- plot stays in editor layout
- FOCAS stays in editor side tab
- variables/errors use embedded NCBottomPanel
end note

note right of BottomWebview
Current VS Code host:
- editor channel panes do not render NCBottomPanel
- workbench panel owns Variables / Errors / FOCAS tabs
- plot remains independent from workbench panel
end note

note bottom of HostBridge
Purpose:
- keep raw acquireVsCodeApi() and
  workbench relay envelope out of main.ts
end note

note bottom of Main
Remaining cleanup in current architecture:
- shared bootstrap still decides host via window probing
- some shared components still branch on VS Code globals directly
- host-specific config assembly is duplicated in extension.ts
end note

note right of VsCodeChannelPane
Current behavior is correct,
but host behavior is still selected
at runtime inside shared UI components.
end note

@enduml